The continue statement in your code is very similar to the break statement in your line of code. The only difference is the break statement ends your code wherever you need the code to break at, everything after the break is not included, the continue statement includes everything after the break. 

In other words, if my code populated a string of numbers as such; 10 - 20 - 30 - 40. And I had a break statement applied to the number 20, the numbers 20, 30, and 40 would not show up in my code, it would just stop at 10. The continue statement allows the numbers 10, 30, and 40 to show up in my code; simply put, continuing my code breaking off the number 20.

